00:00:06.549 --> 00:00:11.440
How to transfer contacts between Android and
Iphone devices

00:00:11.440 --> 00:00:18.440
to transfer contacts from devices supported
by android to iPhone follow these steps

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:29.000
Click on contacts icon on the Android device
then press options and select import / export

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:36.000
then Select export to USB storage
At the end of the export process, return to

00:00:36.100 --> 00:00:45.100
the main screen and click on applications.
- Click on my files, then all files,

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:53.690
sdcard0, after that choose contacts file .vcf
- Click on share via and then on the email

00:00:54.000 --> 00:01:02.250
icon and enter your e-mail address that is
on your iPhone device, then click send.

00:01:02.250 --> 00:01:09.020
- Wait until the sending process is done.
- Check your email on the iPhone and select

00:01:09.020 --> 00:01:16.020
the e-mail that is sent from the Android device
then click on the attached file.

00:01:16.120 --> 00:01:19.000
- You`ll find all the contacts that have been
sent to your iPhone.

00:01:19.100 --> 00:01:24.530
- Click on add contacts and then choose create
new contacts or merge with contacts.

00:01:24.530 --> 00:01:33.100
- Wait until the process ends then press on
contacts icon and you'll find all the contacts

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:35.300
that you have moved.

00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:44.100
To transfer contacts from the iPhone to the
Android device follow these steps:

00:01:44.200 --> 00:01:52.000
log-in to the app store on the iPhone device  
and search for the free app "contacts kit"

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:55.000
download the app and open it

00:01:55.300 --> 00:01:57.090
a message will appear

00:01:57.090 --> 00:02:04.000
tap on the screen to continue tab export then all contacts then next

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:10.200
choose vCard then tap start after finishing click on Email

00:02:11.200 --> 00:02:15.280
then enter you Email address thats on you Android device

00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:23.000
then tap send, after the sending process is done log-in to you email that is on your Android device

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:27.800
and choose the email that was sent to you from you iPhone device

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:33.400
choose attached, then click on the file, where an options screen will appear

00:02:33.400 --> 00:02:38.400
choose phone and wait until the process ends

00:02:39.400 --> 00:02:47.400
go back to the main scree and tap contacts where you will find all you contacts that you transferred

